New York is a state in the northeastern United States,
and is the 27th-most extensive, fourth-most populous,
and seventh-most densely populated U.S. state.
New York is bordered by New Jersey and Pennsylvania
to the south and Connecticut, Massachusetts, and Vermont to the east.
The state has a maritime border in the Atlantic Ocean with Rhode Island,
east of Long Island, as well as an international border with the Canadian
provinces of Quebec to the north and Ontario to the west and north.
The state of New York, with an estimated 19.8 million residents in 2015,
is often referred to as New York State to distinguish it from New York City,
the state's most populous city and its economic hub.